#. Tag: title
#: vm_security.xml:58
#, no-c-format
msgid "Installing Packages and Setting up the Base System"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: vm_security.xml:60
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The confidential compute module provides replacement packages supporting AMD "
"SEV-SNP. To ensure a maximum of compatibility, these packages are based on "
"the code streams from SUSE Linux Enterprise Server."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: vm_security.xml:62
#, no-c-format
msgid "The three components that need to be replaced are:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: vm_security.xml:65
#, no-c-format
msgid "The Linux kernel"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: vm_security.xml:68
#, no-c-format
msgid "QEMU Virtual Machine Monitor"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: vm_security.xml:71
#, no-c-format
msgid "&libvirt; framework"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: vm_security.xml:76
#, no-c-format
msgid "To install the replacement packages, run the command:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: vm_security.xml:77
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"# sudo zypper install coco:kernel-coco coco:qemu coco:libvirt\n"
"      <!-- TO DO: Replace with the actual command.-->\n"
"    "
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: vm_security.xml:80
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"After replacing the packages, you must set up the system with a "
"configuration change to make the AMD SEV-SNP feature ready to use. The IOMMU "
"on the host side must be configured in non-passthrough mode. This is "
"required to prevent peripheral devices from writing to memory which belongs "
"to an encrypted guest and destroy its data integrity. The default IOMMU "
"configuration in SUSE Linux Enterprise Server is <literal>passthrough</"
"literal> mode."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: vm_security.xml:83
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To disable the IOMMU configuration in SUSE Linux Enterprise Server, open the "
"<filename>/etc/default/grub</filename> file and add <literal>iommu=nopt</"
"literal> to the <varname>GRUB_CMDLINE_LINUX_DEFAULT</varname> variable."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: vm_security.xml:85
#, no-c-format
msgid "To update the bootloader configuration, run the command:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: vm_security.xml:86
#, no-c-format
msgid "# update-bootloader"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: vm_security.xml:87
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The system is now ready to be restarted with the confidential computing "
"kernel. It is not selected as the default kernel in the bootloader, so "
"ensure to select it at the boot menu."
msgstr ""

